  "lastUpdatedOn": "2012-11-08",
  "religion": "He is a devout Christian.",
  "politicalViews": "He seems to be fairly non-political aside from being an enthusiastic Obama supporter.",
  "author": "Caitlin Frye",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 1
    },
    {
      "parentId": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Ne-Yo, whose real name is Shaffer Chimere Smith, was born in Camden, Arkansas. He grew up there and in Las Vegas, Nevada."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 2
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "The consensus among Question-Answer sites is that Ne-Yo was born Muslim, but then converted to Christianity during childhood along with his family.",
      "sourceTitle": "What is ne-yo's religion.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://wiki.answers.com/Q/What_is_ne-yo"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " But I could find no information supporting that claim."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 3
    },
    {
      "parentId": 3,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "He has spoken about how Islam is a peaceful religion,",
      "sourceTitle": "NE-YO says Islam is a religion of peace and love.(HARUNYAHYA).",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qme8ZzKVGec"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 3,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " but he is definitely a Christian. When asked about his spirituality he said,"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 4
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 5,
      "parentId": 4
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I pray every day. Not a day goes by that I don't. . . thank God for everything He's done for me. Because I know that without Him none of this is possible. . . . He's the creator of all things. Without God there is nothing.",
      "sourceTitle": "Ne-Yo – Spiritual Side of Hollywood.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_JdUVrM7zTc&feature=related"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 6
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "He's also been known to casually reference God in interviews",
      "sourceTitle": "R&B singer Ne-Yo gets the last laugh.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/03/20/music-neyo-dc-idUSN1818498320070320"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " and wear a crucifix.",
      "sourceTitle": "Ne-yo regrets giving Irreplaceable to Beyonce.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://lovelyti.com/ne-yo-regrets-giving-irreplaceable-to-beyonce/"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " So regardless of his past, Christianity and religious tolerance are both very important to this songwriter.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": 7
    },
    {
      "parentId": 7,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Obama All The Way"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 8
    },
    {
      "parentId": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I couldn't find much information about Ne-Yo's political beliefs aside from his enthusiastic support of Barack Obama. During the president's re-election campaign in 2012, Ne-Yo recorded a song in support of Obama with other high-profile musicians including Johnny Rzeznik and Herbie Hancock.",
      "sourceTitle": "Ne-Yo and other artists lend voices to pro-Obama song.",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/2012/10/26/ne-yo-obama-song/1661139/"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 9
    },
    {
      "parentId": 9,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "For Ne-Yo, the election was too important not to get involved. He said,"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 10
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 11,
      "parentId": 10
    },
    {
      "parentId": 11,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I'm not gonna sit and complain with my friends about what's wrong. I'm gonna get out and make sure that I do something to help fix whatever the hell is wrong. You can't complain if you're not gonna do anything about it.",
      "sourceTitle": "Ne-Yo on Nicki Minaj: 'We Don't Have to Agree on Politics.'",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/ne-yo-wants-to-make-music-and-more-with-nicki-minaj-20120906"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 12
    },
    {
      "parentId": 12,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "One gets the impression that this R&B singer's political fire was lit by the nation's first black president, but he's never said as much. Still, Ne-Yo stuck with Obama after many of his 2008 supporters lost their enthusiasm, so regardless of the reason why, he's a dedicated fan."
    }
  ],
